summary.p: Almost complete codex of the Qurʾān on 144 fol. (one fol. is missing containing surahs 105-101); Shelfmark: HC.MS.00715; Lines per page: 25; Dimensions: 163 x 153 mm; Script style: Maġribī micrography (for the rasm), angular chrysography (sūra headings); Estimated date of production: 12th or early 13th century; Provenance: Muslim Iberia (al-Andalus).

This complete codex of the Qurʾān on parchment written in maġribī script can be dated in the period between 1000 and 1200. Two similar codices are kept by Istanbul Üniversitesi Kütüphanesi A 6755 (Karatay No. 13, Karatay, p. 5) and A 6754 (Karatay No. 14, Karatay, p. 5-6). These Istanbul codices are similar in script style, text design and format. A. 6755 with 148 leaves has a colophon and was written in Cordoba in 1143-44 (538 AH); codex A 6754 (132 leaves) has been written by Muḥammad b. ʿAbdallāh b. ʿAṭūs in Valencia in 1182-83 (578 AH). For this codex one would suggest a similiar date and provenance.
